{
  "texts": [
    "Segmentation involves dividing a dataset or data stream into smaller segments or subsets.",
    "In the context of anomaly detection, segmentation might involve dividing the data stream into smaller chunks to analyze and detect anomalies more effectively within each segment.",
    "The dataset is divided into training and testing sets to evaluate the performance of the anomaly detection model.",
    "In addition, techniques such as oversampling or undersampling have been used to balance the dataset for effective anomaly detection in real-world scenarios where anomalies are rare compared to normal instances.In order to combine the machine learning models, random search technique is used.",
    "Preprocessing the data, including handling missing values, encoding categorical features, and scaling/normalizing numeric features, is performed."
  ]
}